North Korea claimed, on Thursday, that the country is one of the few countries that remain free of coronavirus infection.
As of yesterday, the World Health Organization (WHO) reported 1,051,635 confirmed cases, including 79,332 cases in twenty-four hours since 10am Central European Time (0800 UTC) on 4 April.
In the United States (US), there have been more than 244,000 cases of the coronavirus, resulting in at least 5,900 deaths.
CBS News reports, citing data from Johns Hopkins University, that there are more than 1,000 deaths in the U.S. caused by coronavirus infection.
